mxCell.value: 5 Battery Backup Circuit with Full Redundancy and Minimal Power Draw (Approximately 20 Hours Of 100 rW Maximum Usage)

This circuit was designed to allow for any battery to be lost and minimal single points of failure. Additionally each battery has just a few rW of battery drain to support the circuit. * Main Battery - Active Minimal Draw 16rW, Maximum Output 84 rW * 2nd Battery - Non-Running Draw 9 rW, Active Minimal Draw 16 rW, Maximum Output 84 rW * 3rd Battery - Non-Running Draw 8 rW, Active Minimal Draw 13 rW, Maximum Output 87 rW * 4th Battery - Non-Running Draw 5 rW, Active Minimal Draw 8 rW, Maximum Output 92 rW * 5th Battery - Non-Running Draw 0 rW, Active Minimal Draw 2 rW, Maximum Output 98 rW Note: the Green Light is Optional, you can use any 1rW light or none here, but the draw will be the same
